# Relationship Leaderboard - environment configuration
# Copy this file to .env and fill in values ONLY if you want to enable live
# integrations. The app runs fully functional with mock data if you leave
# every value blank or unset - this is the default and recommended mode for
# local development, demos, and preview deployments.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AI Service (optional)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# When unset, the app uses src/lib/ai-service.ts's MockAIService, which
# produces deterministic, clearly-labeled "Simulated AI" summaries,
# relationship-context extraction, and recommendation copy - no network
# calls, no key required.
#
# To wire up a real OpenAI-backed adapter, set:
#   VITE_AI_PROVIDER=openai
#   VITE_OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
# NOTE: Vite inlines VITE_ values into the client bundle at build time.
# Never put a production secret behind a VITE_ prefix in a real deployment -
# this project intentionally ships only the Mock adapter wired up, and
# documents (in src/lib/ai-service.ts) exactly where a server-side proxy
# route would need to live before a real key is ever used. Treat the two
# lines above as illustrative only.
VITE_AI_PROVIDER=mock
# VITE_OPENAI_API_KEY=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Instantly (cold-email) integration (optional)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# When unset, the app uses src/lib/instantly-service.ts's MockInstantlyService,
# which simulates campaign sends, opens, replies, and bounces via an
# idempotent local webhook simulator - no network calls, no key required.
#
#   VITE_INSTANTLY_PROVIDER=instantly
#   VITE_INSTANTLY_API_KEY=
VITE_INSTANTLY_PROVIDER=mock
# VITE_INSTANTLY_API_KEY=
